On Tue, 2007-02-13 at 11:20 +1100, Ben Nizette wrote:
>   #define array_for_each(element, array) \
> 	for (int __idx = 0; __idx < ARRAY_SIZE((array)); \
> 		__idx++, (element) = &(array[__idx]))
This requires all interior loop code be changed.
